1 including application of the same limits. For purposes of this subsection, mental illnesses are as
2 diagnosed and defined in the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders, DSM-5, or
3 a subsequent edition published by the American Psychiatric Association, except those mental
4 disorders coded in the DSM-5 or subsequent edition as autism spectrum disorder (299.00),
5 substance-related disorders (291.0 through 292.2 and 303.0 through 305.9), those coded as sexual
6 dysfunctions not due to organic disease (302.70 through 302.79), and those coded as "V" codes.
7 For purposes of this subsection, "limits" includes deductibles, coinsurance factors, co-payments,
8 maximum out-of-pocket limits, annual and lifetime dollar limits, and any other dollar limits or
9 fees for covered services.health conditions.
10 (a1) Definitions. – As used The following definitions apply in this section:
11 (1) "Health benefit plan" has the same meaning as Health benefit plan. – As
12 defined in G.S. 58-3-167.
13 (2) "Insurer" has the same meaning as Insurer. – As defined in G.S. 58-3-167.
14 (3) Medical necessity. – As defined in G.S. 58-50-61.
15 (4) "Mental illness" has the same meaning as in G.S. 122C-3(21), with a Mental
16 health condition. – A mental disorder defined in the Diagnostic and Statistical
17 Manual of Mental Disorders, DSM-5, or subsequent editions published by the
18 American Psychiatric Association, except this term does not include those
19 mental disorders coded in the DSM-5 or subsequent editions as autism
20 spectrum disorder (299.00), substance-related disorders (291.0 through 292.9
21 and 303.0 through 305.9), those coded as sexual dysfunctions not due to
