24 (g) Utilization Review. – Nothing in this section prevents an insurer from applying
25 utilization review criteria to determine medical necessity as defined in G.S. 58-50-61 as long as
26 it does so in accordance with all requirements for utilization review programs and medical
27 necessity determinations specified in that section, including the offering of an insurer appeal
28 process and, where applicable, health benefit plan external review as provided for in Part 4 of
29 Article 50 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes.in accordance with G.S. 58-50-61.
30 …
31 (i) Notwithstanding any other provisions of this section, a group health benefit plan that
32 covers both medical and surgical benefits and mental health benefits shall, with respect to the
33 mental health benefits, comply with all Federal Law Applies. – All applicable standards of
34 Subtitle B of Title V of Public Law 110-343, known as the Paul Wellstone and Pete Domenici
35 Mental Health Parity and Addiction Equity Act of 2008, and the applicable regulations, as
36 amended.amended, and other relevant federal law shall apply to health benefit plans.
37 …."
38 SECTION 3.3. The Revisor of Statutes shall replace the phrase "chemical
39 dependency" with the phrase "substance use disorder" in all of the following statutes:
40 (1) G.S. 58-51-16(a).
41 (2) G.S. 58-51-40(a).
42 (3) G.S. 58-51-55(b).
43 (4) G.S. 58-65-90(b).
44 (5) G.S. 58-67-75(b).
45 SECTION 3.4. All of the following are repealed:
46 (1) G.S. 58-51-50.
47 (2) Subdivision (a)(2) and subsection (c) of G.S. 58-51-55.
48 (3) G.S. 58-65-75.
49 (4) Subdivision (a)(2) and subsection (c) of G.S. 58-65-90.
50 (5) G.S. 58-67-70.
51 (6) Subdivision (a)(2) and subsection (c) of G.S. 58-67-75.
