1 SECTION 3.5. G.S. 58-3-192(a)(2) reads as rewritten:
2 "(2) Autism spectrum disorder. – As defined by the most recent edition of the
3 Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (DSM) or the most
4 recent edition of the International Statistical Classification of Diseases and
5 Related Health Problems. Autism spectrum disorder is not considered a
6 mental illness health condition, as defined in G.S. 58-3-220, 58-51-55, or a
7 mental illness, as defined in G.S. 58-51-55, 58-65-90, or 58-67-75."
8 SECTION 3.6.(a) G.S. 58-56-26 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
9 "(e) Notwithstanding any provision of this Article to the contrary, all requirements relating
10 to the coverage of prescription drugs and pharmacy services under this Chapter that apply to
11 health benefit plans are applicable to a third-party administrator in the same way they are
12 applicable to an insurer."
13 SECTION 3.6.(b) Article 56A of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by
14 adding a new section to read:
15 "§ 58-56A-55. Health benefit plan requirements applicable.
16 All requirements relating to the coverage of prescription drugs and pharmacy services under
17 this Chapter that apply to health benefit plans are applicable to a pharmacy benefits manager in
18 the same way they are applicable to an insurer."
19 SECTION 3.7. This Part is effective when it becomes law and applies to insurance
20 contracts issued, amended, or renewed on or after that date.
21
22 PART IV. EFFECTIVE DATE
23 SECTION 4.1. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
24 law.
